==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*driosa-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[driosan]] (Dutch [[druisen]]), Gothic [[𐌳𐍂𐌹𐌿𐍃𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'dre:ozan/

===Verb===
{{Unicode|(ġe)'''drēosan'''}} (class II strong)
# to [[fall]], to [[decline]], to [[collapse]]
#:''Dreoseþ deaw and ren'': dew and rain both fall.

